140
00:05:46,212 --> 00:05:49,045
All right, just stop this.
This is nonsense.

141
00:05:49,115 --> 00:05:50,548
You're not over.

142
00:05:50,616 --> 00:05:53,710
Look, you're a
striking man with
strong features,

143
00:05:53,786 --> 00:05:57,153
eyes that women
want to do
cannonballs into.

144
00:05:57,323 --> 00:06:01,282
You have great posture
and penmanship
the likes I've never seen.

145
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:04,558
No, I have officially
hit rock bottom.

146
00:06:04,630 --> 00:06:06,621
A month ago,
I got this case, right?

147
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:09,532
A healthy <i>4</i>2- year-old
astronomer dies.

148
00:06:09,635 --> 00:06:11,535
Doesn't drink, doesn't
smoke, spends all day

149
00:06:11,604 --> 00:06:14,869
in an ergonomically-designed
chair, charting the night sky.

150
00:06:14,941 --> 00:06:17,774
Natural causes,
that's what the Coroner
comes back with.

151
00:06:17,844 --> 00:06:20,074
Does a full autopsy.
No red flags. Nothing.

152
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:23,843
I know he was murdered.
I just can't...

153
00:06:25,918 --> 00:06:27,852
What? What?
What is this?

154
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:28,978
...prove it!

155
00:06:29,822 --> 00:06:31,722
The department won't even
let me pursue it.

156
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:33,816
Come on, you'll
figure it out.

157
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:37,920
No, I won't. I can't.
And I've accepted that.

158
00:06:38,364 --> 00:06:40,264
All right, look, Lassy...

159
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:44,697
Carlton,

160
00:06:45,972 --> 00:06:48,634
I believe in you.
I really do.

161
00:06:48,841 --> 00:06:51,401
You just gotta trust
your instincts.

162
00:06:51,477 --> 00:06:52,569
(SHRIEKING)

163
00:06:52,678 --> 00:06:54,168
(LAUGHING)

164
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:56,078
I just got engaged!

165
00:06:56,149 --> 00:06:59,550
Oh, my God!
Thank you! Thank you!
Thank you!

166
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,344
(BOTH SCREAMING)

167
00:07:01,421 --> 00:07:02,979
I got engaged!

168
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:04,248
(LAUGHING)

169
00:07:04,323 --> 00:07:07,121
SHAWN: I'll never, ever
see you again. Bye.

170
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:08,884
(THUDDING)

171
00:07:08,961 --> 00:07:11,088
Stick with it, Lassy. You...

172
00:07:13,032 --> 00:07:14,795
You can solve this thing.

173
00:07:16,135 --> 00:07:18,160
You're halfway there already.

174
00:07:23,843 --> 00:07:27,438
<i>I know, you know</i>
<i>That I'm not telling the truth</i>

175
00:07:27,513 --> 00:07:30,676
<i>I know, you know</i>
<i>They just don't have any proof</i>

176
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:33,913
<i>Embrace the deception</i>
<i>Learn how to bend</i>

177
00:07:33,986 --> 00:07:38,821
<i>Your worst inhibitions</i>
<i>tend to psych you out</i>
<i>in the end</i>

178
00:07:44,697 --> 00:07:46,392
(WHISPERS) Check this out.
GUS: What?

179
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:47,956
Hey, Lassy.

180
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:49,260
What is it, Spencer?

181
00:07:49,368 --> 00:07:50,835
How you doing?
You okay?

182
00:07:51,571 --> 00:07:53,869
All right. I'll bite.
What's the joke?

183
