Well, okay.
Wine at weddings.

190
00:08:06,786 --> 00:08:08,481
Occasional snifter
of brandy.

191
00:08:08,921 --> 00:08:10,445
Maybe a single-malt scotch.

192
00:08:10,523 --> 00:08:11,649
Sounds like drinking to me.

193
00:08:11,724 --> 00:08:15,455
Spencer, why don't you stop
making up stories, okay?
They're obviously bogus.

194
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:18,122
Okay, so you were not
at Tom Blair's Pub last night?

195
00:08:18,264 --> 00:08:19,925
I don't even know
who Tom Blair is.

196
00:08:19,999 --> 00:08:23,127
Mmm-hmm.
And how'd you get that sweet
bruise on your forehead?

197
00:08:23,469 --> 00:08:24,493
I had an altercation.

198
00:08:24,570 --> 00:08:25,867
Yes, with a table.

199
00:08:25,938 --> 00:08:26,996
CARLTON: With a suspect.

200
00:08:27,073 --> 00:08:30,270
If we're done,
I would really like
to move on with my day.

201
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,640
I get it.

202
00:08:31,978 --> 00:08:33,570
Yesterday was

203
00:08:34,046 --> 00:08:35,479
