He wanted to try for a baby.

273
00:11:20,579 --> 00:11:22,206
He was a good man.

274
00:11:22,415 --> 00:11:24,144
Thanks again for
coming in, Mary.

275
00:11:24,216 --> 00:11:25,979
No problem, Kkarlton.

276
00:11:26,085 --> 00:11:28,053
If we uncover any...
Carlton?

277
00:11:28,587 --> 00:11:30,612
Yes, Karlton, with a "K."

278
00:11:30,690 --> 00:11:32,590
Two "K"s.
The second one
is silent.

279
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:37,693
May I speak to you
privately in your
office, Kkarlton?

280
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:38,957
Certainly.

281
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:40,555
We'll be in touch.
Thanks.

282
00:11:41,567 --> 00:11:44,365
What are you doing reopening
the Vallery case?

283
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:46,962
Reopening? Come on.
That word has
so many syllables.

284
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:49,132
That case was determined
not to be a case,

285
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,472
despite Detective Lassiter's
best efforts.

286
00:11:51,644 --> 00:11:52,838
Shawn!

287
00:11:53,312 --> 00:11:57,043
Now, I need a
whole lot of an
explanation from you,

288
00:11:57,116 --> 00:11:59,880
because, although you do
make me laugh occasionally,

289
00:11:59,952 --> 00:12:01,317
impersonating an officer is...

290
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,752
Impersonating an officer?
Please.

291
00:12:02,822 --> 00:12:05,290
I told that woman
I was in accounts payable.

292
00:12:05,357 --> 00:12:07,052
Shawn, come clean.

293
00:12:08,194 --> 00:12:10,754
I would like to solve
this case for Lassiter.

294
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:11,888
He'll never allow it.

295
00:12:11,964 --> 00:12:13,261
That's why he can't
know I'm involved.

296
00:12:13,332 --> 00:12:15,766
I figure I can
guide him through
this thing, right?

297
00:12:15,835 --> 00:12:17,735
Build him up,
get him back
on his feet again.

298
00:12:17,803 --> 00:12:19,293
You're serious?
Yeah.

299
00:12:19,371 --> 00:12:20,633
Why?

300
00:12:20,806 --> 00:12:24,071
I just feel like
